Package se.code77.jq

JQ promise implementation

See: Description

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    JQ.DeferredHandler<V>
    Callback interface used by deferrer to get access to the Deferred object
    Promise<V>
    A Promises/A+ style promise offering simple, chainable asynchronous invocations.
    Promise.OnFulfilledCallback<V,NV>
    Callback interface for resolved/fulfilled promises.
    Promise.OnRejectedCallback<NV>
    Callback interface for rejected promises.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    JQ
    JQ is a promise implementation in Java, aiming to conform to the Promises/A+ specification.
    JQ.Deferred<V>
    A deferred object is used by methods implementing asynchronous operations exposed by promises.
    JQ.OnFulfilledVoidCallback<V>
    Convenience for the case where you want to transform a promised value to void, i.e., ((Void)null), for example if an operation you need to wait upon returns a promise for a String but you simply want to return an empty promise used for observing when the complete operation is complete.
    Promise.StateSnapshot<V>
    The state snapshot of a promise as returned by Promise.inspect().
    Value<V>
    A simple wrapped value implementing the Future interface.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    Promise.State
    State of a promise.
  • Exception Summary 
    Exception Description
    Promise.UnhandledRejectionException
    An exception thrown by a promise which is terminated without any rejection callback.
